      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The movement explicitly defines \"harmful norms\" based on evidence of systemic oppression, which naturally excludes those who reject that framework, but this is a feature, not a bug, of a society committed to correcting deep-seated injustices. If we wait for everyone to agree on what is harmful before acting, we will never dismantle the very structures that silence marginalized people in the first place. True progress requires the courage to challenge deeply held beliefs when they cause real-world damage, even if it creates friction with those who refuse to see the problem.",
      "source": "target",
